This year, women have won the Nobel prizes in all disciplines, except in physics.
Five record women have taken in Stockholm today from the hands of Sweden's King Carl XVI Gustaf this year's Nobel prizes in the technical categories and for literature.
In addition to the four scientists was under the German writer Herta Müller, including.
The Nobel Prize for medicine have two American Biologinnen, Elizabeth Blackburn and Carol Greider, together with her compatriot Jack Szostak for research in the area.
The prize for chemistry has the Israeli Ada Jonath, together with the Americans Venkatraman Ramakrishnan and Thomas Steitz, for clarification of the Ribosom structure and function.
The last Laureatin the Nobel Prize for economics, the American, her compatriot Elinor Ostrom and Oliver Williamson for analysis of the economic report.
The only specialist category, in which no woman in this year, received a Nobel Prize in physics.
This prize today, the scientist Charles Kao for research in the glass fibre - area and George Smith, together with Willard Boyl for the CCD - chip - invention, which is the basis of all Digitalkammeras, fax machines or astronomical pipes.
Each of the winners received the diploma, the Nobelmedaile and certificate on the acquisition of the prize money.
The totals in each category of ten million Swedish kronor.
If there are several winners in each category, the prize money will be divided among them.
