Czech discovery: a substance, which is also in gestählten ' HIV viruses
The team of Czech and German scientists testing new compounds, which are intended to prevent the spread of HIV virus in the body.
The main advantage of improved substance is that he is also in the viruses, which are resistant to drugs.
This fact against the disadvantage that the link to normal virus variants is not as strong as one of the existing medicines.
The disease AIDS cannot be cured.
The patients, the drug but can prolong the lives and prevent the proliferation of the HIV virus in the body.
But their income is accompanied by a whole range of side effects.
Incomplete suppression of the virus, also has the development sg. Resistentviren, against the no drugs are more effective.
The work of the experts from the three institutions of the Academy of Sciences, from the VSCHT (chemically - technological University) Prague and the University of Heidelberg opens the way, how to deal with the virus - resistant.
They have proven that the substances on the protein known as Metalokarborane substance, which is responsible for the expansion of the HIV Viruses.
The Metalokarborane are links from Bor, hydrogen, carbon and cobalt.
These compounds block the virus reproduction in other ways than all drugs used today, so they can overcome the resistance problem.
In their work, the scientists to new ' improved ties, which have been prepared on the basis of knowledge of the molecular mechanism of their attachment to the viral protein substance.
The Metalokarborane have a unique three - dimensional structure: two vielfächige cages from, hydrogen and carbon atoms, and through a metal atom, in this case, cobalt, are linked.
Heimtückisches and constant virus
HIV Protease is protein substance of the HIV virus, which is essential for the life cycle of the virus.
Without the HIV - caused by the HIV virus would not mature Infektionsvirenpartikel.
If we eliminate the HIV Protease, we call the propagation of the virus in the body of the patient, the scientists in the press report, by the Institute for organic chemistry and biochemistry of the Academy of Sciences CR.
In the work, in the Science paper was published in the Journal of Medicinal Chemistry, the scientists describe all ranks of the compounds, in which two couples cages (see table) by a brief organic chain, which is then systematically further changed.
A little weaker, but reliable
The impact of this series of substances against the HIV Protease wurdne tested in Reagenzglas, even against their steady (resistant) variants, which were won by HIV - infected patients.
The impact of the Metalokarborane in the usual enzyme variant is not as strong as in the clinical use of medicines, but they do not lose their effect on the Resistentvarianten, against which the drugs are often ineffective.
The unique effect mechanism and its other properties, such as the biological and chemical stability, low toxicity and the possibility of further chemical ways, the Metalokarboranen to interesting links for further on the development of effective drugs against HIV research, says Pavlina Rezacova, head of the laboratory for structural biology of the Institute for organic chemistry and biochemistry and molecular genetics of the Institute for the National Academy of Sciences.
