The new map of the CD (Czech railways) will be fewer trains for roughly the same fare.
The Czech railways stopped or restricted from 13 December some less full speed and local trains, other links will be strengthened.
The whole transport volume will be reduced from the day of the new road map compared with today at two percent.
Most tariffs incl. Basic and Kundenfahrtarif will not be changed.
Several link opportunities in the capital, for example, the residents of the Ostrava region, the railways for this type Pendolino trains.
The train will no longer to Bratislava (the) .
Less fast trains will also be on the Prague - Pisek, Budweis, in principle, the direct links from Prague to Letohrad.
The biggest reduction plans the railway in the district of Hradec Kralove (King Graz) , for a total of eight percent, to an increase in Prague and environment.
Be lifted two night trains on the route from Prague Tabor - Budweis and on some days in the week of the operation of some fast trains on the route from Prague - Pisek - reduced.
One of the biggest changes include the introduction of the new Direktverkehrsweges from Milovice after Prague, now have the inhabitants of Milovice in Lysa nad Labem.
It is the fifteenth route of suburban transport system Esko, whose opening thanks to the rail electrification from Lysa nad Labem after is possible.
The long distance routes in the capital will be in the target station Prague main station.
The CD is more lines SC Pendolino between Prague and Ostrava and the trains after Sumperk/Jesenik in the space of two hours.
With the Pendolino passengers since 13 December can no longer go to Bratislava.
