The experts are also on the vaccination procedure.
New vaccination
Free Vaccines for August - children
From January can be vaccinated against Pneumokokken free of charge, on 2 August last year and later were born.
The condition st that they have not received a vaccine dose.
Anyone who has begun with the vaccine in the last year or earlier, must also pay for themselves.
The first dose of vaccine should be between 3 and 5 month of life of the child.
Already last year, a quarter of the families to vaccinate their children against Pneumokokken.
The parents paid 1,600 crowns and more for a dose.
For the vaccination of the youngest children are four doses required.
As a whole, the experts estimate that the health insurance for the vaccination doses of 300,000-450 kroner per year.
They save but in the treatment, which would need the children without vaccination.
Until now, the state for all land vaccination of children around 500,000 per year.
The compulsory vaccination was introduced with the so - called Janota package.
Pneumokokken Mittelohrentzündung, but also cause serious infections including Gehirnhautentzündungen and blood poisoning.
By Pneumokokkeninfektionen die in our investigation in hospitals per year up to 28 children up to the age of 10 years.
Outside of the Czech Republic was the duty - vaccination of children against Pneumokokken in some 40 countries.
Will the vaccine be mandatory?
At the same time, it is said that this vaccine could be in the future.
From January to paid by the insurance and be voluntary.
