Although banned in Norway, America and Russia, the Erlegen in Greenland and Canada, where hunters in helicopters and motor sleigh - travelling Inuit powerful assault rifles to express their prey on the route.
Ironically, in the waters in the north of this two hunting nations the ice longest remain.
In his new book " after the ice " (original title " after the Ice ") Alun Anderson, a former editor of science magazine New Scientist ", a clear and disturbing description of the science of the Arctic and a packenden insight into how the future could develop.
This is Not to say that scientists have all the answers.
Neither Climate scientists still Ozeanografen can adequately explain the speed of change.
