The signature meeting on Friday evening " welcomed " the Secretary of state for transport, Dominique Bussereau the agreement, which was launched on Wednesday morning after several weeks of negotiations.
After a second night of negotiations, the Verhandelnden on early Friday morning in the hope to sign the agreement at the end of the morning.
And despite the fact that the three employers ' federation (FNTR, and OTRE) had left the meeting.
However, it has taken more than six hours from the start of the meeting at 11:00 a. m. until the conclusion of the agreement and p. m., the agreement was signed.
The conflict " the company would have very much harm " and " it was feared that he would affect the holidays at the end of the year, " Bussereau.
The agreement provides for a wage increase of 4% for the lowest wages (local and regional road transport) and 2.9% for the highest wage groups (international transport) .
The hourly rate for workers with the lowest wages rising from 8.72 on 9.06 euros.
" It is not very much, but once we start small, " the first Clos (FO) .
The activists are now instructed not to block the supply centers.
" it will probably always be some however, are not satisfied with the agreement, " he added.
The TLF - chairman Philippe Grillot spoke of a " good agreement ", although it was difficult to give these wage increases in the face of international competition ".
According to him, the increase in 170 euros a month for the low and 100 to 120 euros for the high wages.
" This agreement is based on the common sense and respect for the employees, " maxim Dumont (CFDT) , while Thierry Douine (CFTC) spoke of " a historic agreement ".
Richard Jaubert (CGT) said " an acceptable compromise. "
The agreement also provides for an increase in the cost of travel by 3% and the upholding of the overall budget for road transport in the first half of 2010, which will enable it, in particular, the issue of 13 monthly salary and the modernisation of collective agreements.
M. Bussereau recalled that " the drop of the charges for the employers to the tune of 100 million the subject of an amendment to the government on the finances for 2009, which was adopted during the night from Thursday to Friday by the National Assembly.
The government calls " an identical " vote by the Senate.
