Turkish Constitutional Court resolves pro - Kurdish party. decision with serious consequences
The Turkish Constitutional Court on Friday announced the dissolution of the pro - Kurdish main party in the country; a decision on the immediate angry demonstrations in the Kurdish community in the south - east of the country and in Istanbul.
This decision threatens the work of the government, which is trying to reach out to the Kurdish community to the 25 years of conflict to an end.
The " party for a democratic society " (DTP) was dissolved, because they had become a " site for activities for the independence of the state and its indivisible unity, " the President of the Constitutional Court Hasim Kiliç four days after the decision to the press.
According to Kiliç would be the decision taken unanimously by 11 judges, with a majority of seven votes would have been needed to impose the dissolution. In addition, he pointed out that 37 of the leadership of the party, including the chairman and the parliamentarian Aysel Tugluk, for the period of five years from the political scene.
Furthermore, the judge announced the lifting of parliamentary immunity, the Türk and Tugluk enjoy, and the seizure of the assets of the party.
The DTP now has 21 seats in Parliament (550) .
The party leader said before the verdict that the Members of Parliament rather than to meet parliamentarians.
The decision followed a in 2007 by the prosecutor of the Turkish federal court Abdurrahman Yalçinkaya. He accused the DTP, the " instructions " of the Kurdistan Workers ' Party (PKK) , which is considered a terrorist organisation by Ankara and many other countries.
Many observers believe that the DTP is the legal political showcase the PKK rebels.
The party, " no link " to the PKK, but refuses to describe this as a terrorist organisation and calls on the government to negotiate.
The verdict of the Constitutional Court transmits the government, which is seeking to accommodate the Kurdish community and a series of measures to strengthen the rights of the Kurds, the support of the PKK, the Kurds and to put an end to the conflict.
The leaders of the DTP confirm that a break - up could lead to a resurgence of tensions in south - where many demonstrations against the conditions of detention of the PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan in recent weeks had led to clashes with the police.
Since the announcement of the court gathered thousands of demonstrators outside the premises of the DTP in the city of Diyarbakir in south - east, which is populated by Kurds.
The forces of tear - gas grenades and water cannons, when the protesters began to throw Molotov cocktails and stones.
Hundreds of people marched in Istanbul.
After the verdict, was that the decision of the court " further deepen the despair ".
" Turkey can this (Kurdish, Anm. editorial) question not on the basis of the ban of a party, " he told the press.
The government, consisting of a party that has emerged from the Islamist movement, regretted the decision.
" We oppose in principle against the closure of the parties.
That does not solve the problems, " Energy Minister Taner Yildiz.
" This decision is a frustrating the democratic opening, which was promoted by the government, " the political market observers Ahmet island.
" It is obviously a reaction from the PKK, " he added.
On Thursday, the PKK to an attack in which three days earlier, seven soldiers were killed in the north of the country. It was one of the most brutal attacks of the past few months.
New Silicon Valley
For many years it was a secret city, for Western visitors inaccessible.
Selenograd, one in ten districts of the capital, Moscow, was in the Soviet Union, a strict bewachter location for secret defence research.
Today, the community with its 216 000 inhabitants, 37 kilometres from the centre of Moscow, as " Russian Silicon Valley. "
Major research and production facilities for micro and nano electronics are here.
Since September 2008, representatives Selenograds contacts to Frankfurt science location Riedberg - with the Uniinstituten and the firms of the Frankfurt Innovation centre (FIZ) .
There were several mutual visits and on Wednesday Selenograd and Riedberg in Frankfurt signed a " protocol on closer cooperation. "
The Moscow Deputy Mayor Yuri Rosljak and prefect Anatoly Smirnov of Selenograd led the Russian delegation, Planungsdezernent Edwin Black.
2010 will be representatives of the FIZ and small and medium - sized enterprises in the science Foschungsschwerpunkts for a seminar after Selenograd.
Scientific exchanges
It is a continuous scientific exchanges.
But it is also about economic relations.
The FIZ firms will be allowed to gain a foothold in the growing Russian market.
Conversely, want to Russian science firms contracts in Germany.
Selenograd is the seat of major Russian research institutes and companies.
These include the Moscow Institute for technology, the big corporations and Rosssijskaja Elektronika.
The community was founded in 1958 as a so - called " socialist plan city " for the defence research.
Selenograd (literally translated as " green city ") got its name from the forested hills landscape, in which the research institutes are embedded.
Stuttgart brake
The dimension of Stuttgart 21 is not high enough.
For the supporters of the project is purely and simply " the new heart of Europe ".
Right. S21 is much more than the deeper a train station, more than a gigantic construction project, which the City of Baden - Württemberg capital for a decade in chaos.
Stuttgart 21 is from the spirit of the 1980's.
Head stations with tracks in the middle of the city, was seen at the time as a technical fossils of the 19th century, as bremsklötze of a modern rail transport, since it took a lot of time, locomotives from behind.
In short, to go further.
And that is why the head stations should disappear: in Frankfurt and Munich.
And in Stuttgart: a transit station, about half - way through the trans - European rail main route between Paris and Budapest/Bratislava - so the slogan of " heart of Europe ".
S21 will now actually addressed, although the visions of the 1980s are no longer compatible with reality.
Even very ambitious planners have realised that it is in the hessischen and the Bavarian city is almost impossible to implement the Tiefer.
Head stations have no entry and exit problem any more, however, since there are modern locomotives and tax cars at both ends.
However, Stuttgart 21 and the ICE - neubaustrecke after Ulm is now being addressed.
State and local politicians have.
The train with power, because the risks of the largest of the Republic of taxpayers and not the state company.
Städtebaulich the project is still reasonably justified.
It creates new city area, which is the computer generated graphics of the planners - with a lot of green.
For the transport system S21 is harmful.
The transit station and the development are intended for passenger transport, which - typically 1980s - huge growth.
At that time, there was not the competition from low - cost carriers.
Modern transport policy, but it must first to strengthen the freight transport, because the transport by rail is much cleaner than by lorries on the roads.
But the new route is not because of intense climbs for freight trains.
Much more serious is that S21 indirectly affects many other rail projects.
Good six billion euros in Schwäbischen are buried.
That is the official number.
Experts believe that 10 to 15 billion for realistic.
What is clear is that in the next decade will lack the money to other hubs and Engstellen the network.
A total of 60 major projects are on the list of the transport ministry.
One of the most important is the development of the 180 - kilometer route through the Rhine valley.
Since 1987, is being built on the route in slow motion.
Is urgently needed, right here on the tube.
But S21 will act as a brake.
The Rheintalstrecke is the real bottleneck for international freight transport: right in the heart of Europe.
