Dream worlds
Some people see in wachem state images and hear voices, others do not see or hear.
Not only in mental health and drug binge blurs the boundaries between fantasy and reality.
As long as it is happening in their sleep, everything is in order.
If we with closed eyes in our dark rooms, we must likes the wildest ideas and Phantasiegebilden.
Anyone who witnessed in a guard traumartige conditions, things others do not see or hear in the modern Western world as crazy or, at least as a Sonderling.
But such images and voices arise not only in mental health or drug binge.
Blame our imagination: the same neural processes that enable us to design houses, paint pictures or to write novels, sometimes to ensure that the boundaries between dream, fantasy and reality.
Dream suddenly changed Wachbewusstseinszustände can occur in many different forms, in the best case we call them visions, in the worst case of madness.
Even if cause and effect may differ, the vision of the Mystikerin Hildegard of Bingen, the drug experiences of New - Age - prophet Carlos Castaneda, schamanische Entrückungszustände, psychosis and hallucinations similar processes.
Hallucinations or delusions, if the balance of the neural messenger substances of the brain - especially dopamine, serotonin and noradrenaline, Acetylcholin - and the interaction of various parts of the brain.
Complex hallucinations and wahnhafte thoughts are very often during a schizophrenic psychoses.
The gravity has no power over him
The context of madness and dream, philosophers and doctors since ancient times.
Aristotle understood hallucinations as a form of the dream in the state, Wilhelm Griesinger, one of the founders of the modern psychiatry, noted a " great similarity of the mistaken one with a dream, the dream of Sigmund Freud was " a climate, with all the inconsistencies, Wahnbildungen, of such a ".
It is the autumn of 2001, when Henning T. turned into a character.
His body is two dimensions and quietschbunt.
The gravity has no power over him, he is hanging in the bedroom ceiling.
He senses a kick.
Behind him devil shape with blood red, distorted Fratzen, zähnefletschend.
They chase him, him with serious, inflammatory boots, throwing him against the walls, he feels the pain of the whole body.
Noisy, malicious voices roar from walls and radio.
He can no longer bear the voices that attack and insult him.
Henning T. snaps two cable from the stereo, knotet a noose and consolidating them in a hole in the ceiling.
It is rising on a loudspeaker and sets the noose around the neck.
Jumping.
The noose resolves itself.
This should be a lesson to you, the voices in trommelfellzerfetzendem choir, " walk in the clinic and let you cure! "
Today, Henning T. is 40 years old, he has seen six acute psychosis, the last 2 years ago, the first in nearly 20 years.
It was triggered by LSD.
His diagnosis is schizoaffektive - paranoid psychosis, moreover, he is bi - low, he takes medication against depression, mania, the schizophrenia.
He has learned to live with his disease, for three years, he is married.
In the fears I have seen worst fear and deepest despair, he says.
The images are cruel reality
About one percent of the population at least once in life with schizophrenia, in psychiatric hospitals, it is treated as the second most common illness after the depression.
In an acute schizophrenic psychoses affected mostly can no longer distinguish between internal and external world, they are in a state of übererregten to hallucinations, sizes, relationships or paranoia.
The vote is particularly prevalent hearing voices, or comment on dialogisieren.
Optical hallucinations are not rare.
The person is not important to separate more trivial, the brain can no longer ausfiltern disturbing signals, the awareness is awash with impressions.
As the dream opens the psychosis the floodgates for a flood of ideas and fantasies, the deeper awareness classes.
The reality of perception in the climate is subjektzentriert, says Professor Thomas fox, Oberarzt the clinic for General psychiatry in Universitätsklinikum Heidelberg.
The Schizophrene finds itself in the middle of it, everything has a significance to him.
At the same time, he is in a passive role, he will, as in a dream, overwhelmed by what has happened and not active.
Schizophrenic feel so often threatened, controlled and manipulated.
A reality is not possible, the images are cruel reality, wake up.
Once in a lifetime to have experienced a Halluzination
Unlike in the dream, says fox, " but the sinnliche and spatial structure of reality, which is perceived in the psychosis, basically. "
The obsessive thoughts and hallucinations were rooted in reality, the alienation of the Erlebens will take place in real terms.
Why is our brain antics, researchers is still a mystery.
Exceptional conditions can lead in every person that he loses the reality in the short term, says fox.
But not everyone will develop a climate.
There seems to be a genetic predisposition to schizophrenia, but twin studies have shown that the genes are not the only determinants.
Researchers assume that involved minimal brain damage.
We suspect that the neuronale maturation of the brain will be disrupted at an early stage of development, a viral infection of the mother during pregnancy, for example, fox said.
But it remains a mystery, as the disruption of the neural system, the manifestiere not also first over many years.
Environmental factors also play a role, stress or traumatic experiences can be a trigger for psychosis, if the choice is there.
Also halluzinogene drugs can trigger psychosis, because they intervene in the transmitter system.
If our brain is overheating
The crazy, Psychotiker suffer from their hallucinations and expensive drugs, in order to get rid of them, others are, in order to get money for drugs, says the Lübecker psychology professor Erich caste.
Whether related images as pleasant or unpleasant, is often just a matter of the position.
Caste collects for ten years, reports of hallucinations and last year, he has his results in the book " The unreal world in our head. "
Hallucinations are among the typical effects of psychosis, but also of surprising many other diseases.
These include mental disorders, such as borderline or depression often diseases such as migraine, epilepsy, multiple sclerosis, Alzheimer's disease and Schädelhirntraumata.
Surprisingly, hallucinates under certain conditions, even the brain healthy people.
Hallucinations, so castes, from memory content, which would normally be withheld.
They arise when, in which are sensory processing, discouraged or too little; if our brain or even if stimulation.
Drugs can trigger this state as well as brain damage or a psychosis.
But also appeal of deprivation, stress, pain or other mental conditions.
In recent studies, up to a third of those polled said that at least once in a lifetime to have experienced hallucinations.
In the summer of 2005, Sarah K. 16 years old, she lives in a small town in Mecklenburg - Western Pomerania and visited the school.
A normal girl, really.
If it were not for the images and voices.
In the break, it can happen that a schlaksiger boy with long, dark hair.
If he says, look at the classmates surprisingly - no one else sees or hears these boys.
They think the timid girl for a versponnene Tagträumerin, but Sarah K. not dreaming, it knows it.
She is awake, they hear and see these boys, just as the girls in the bank in addition to hear and see.
You can even feel his presence, at least for moments.
A pleasant feeling is that they may be the boys.
Am I crazy? , asks them sometimes.
But she knows that this boy and the other images are not real, and then disappear again.
At night, the most frightening phenomena
The images are Often also a burden.
If you are sitting in the class room, they can follow the teaching material sometimes because the teachers in their eyes and ears just a new classmates, while he explained for all other hearing and visible on the table mathematical equations.
At night, the phenomena are frightening.
If they are in their dark room to sleep, which is far too little and far too late, they can often not distinguish whether she is awake or dreams, whether the pictures you see, the Fratzen or the girl with the arms and legs, before their open or closed eyes.
Let me in, they are the characters.
Parents and friends told them nothing, which would be crazy.
Autumn 2009. Sarah K. is now 20 years old.
In the past year she has insisted the baccalaureate and lives with her friend.
A year ago, the hallucinations.
Since the Internet contact with the psychologists castes, she knows that she is not crazy.
Cow is also a work of art from despair
If someone is socially isolated or suffered sensory deprivation, in all probability, hallucinations, after a while.
I suspect that the brain is underemployed, and even for his entertainment.
Sarah K., a Einzelkind, had as a little girl, fear of other children, often played alone.
Their hallucinations began with 13, when they learned that the man they dad, since they can think, is not their leiblicher father.
As visual and acoustic hallucinations the same brain areas are active, the real impressions and sounds, it is affected as Sarah K. difficult to distinguish images and reality. " every experience, " says caste, " will take place in the brain, the reality is there.
Hallucinations are also images of the brain, that is why they are so real. "
Also night dream images of caste as a form of hallucinations.
The hallucinations of healthy do not differ fundamentally from those of an acute psychosis.
In contrast to Schizophrenen are mentally healthy in the situation, their images as unreal.
Caste advises his patients, therefore, the hallucinations as a special ability.
Border state between dream and hallucinations
In our world too much bewusstseinszentrierten imaginary experience is, unfortunately, says Michael Schmidt - Degenhard, professor in Heidelberg and chief doctor of the clinic for psychiatry and psychotherapy of Florence Nightingale hospital in Düsseldorf.
A psychosis is a serious, painful disease, but it also has creative - is also a work of art out of desperation.
Schmidt - Degenhard has researched the so - called oneiroide experience form, a particular form of traumartig modified guard awareness.
Oneiroide are highly complex, detailed quasi - dreams, the Erlebende for real and he cannot distinguish downstream from the.
The oneiroide awareness state in trauma or illness extreme situations, for example, in Polyradikulitis patients experience in full awareness of a motor paralysis.
If a person of self - and world loss is threatened by continuing replaces the life - threatening reality through their own imaginary world, the decoupled from reality, says Schmidt - Degenhard.
A kind of border state between dream and hallucinations.
Since the deal with a situation in the reality is not possible, a world of change is taking place, but the real situation in the imagination.
An intensive form of Sinn Foundation and making itself in an intolerable situation, the people own ability, not submerged in a loss of loss.
Everything is real, later in the memory
The devoted art historian Peter Cornelius Claussen describes his Oneiroid - experiences in his book " change of heart " as a bailout of the soul.
He is 49 years old when his consciousness after a heart valve operation, followed by a heart transplant on travel, while his body to the intensive care unit for Bewegungslosigkeit.
Claussen, a in a selbstgeschaffene created world, other times and places: he is seen as bettlägerigen, old man, on board a Zugsanatoriums, a robot on his health.
He lives in the early Middle Ages, among the drugs from blood.
By a Greeks on the motorcycle in his home country, surfing with his hospital bed in the Firnschnee the Alps and a Korean Mafioso.
He is completely in the imagined, everything is real, later in the memory.
These internal travel for Claussen differ fundamentally from any dream.
Dream is a different state, he describes his experience.
In contrast, the memories from mental travel and even after years in minor details.
More and more even than real memories.
The intensity of this Erlebens goes beyond the horizon of our other secular life experience, says the psychiatrist hard.
Ultimately, show Oneiroide, psychoses, hallucinations and how fragile our internal copies of external reality in the guards
Any change of status, say the psychologist caste, " can lead to a Verformung of what we call reality. "
An experience which can also be rewarding.
