Michelin and Fesvial together for the use of the Helms
The tyre manufacturer Michelin has, in cooperation with the Spanish Foundation for Traffic safety (Fesvial) a campaign to promote the helmet use, especially among the younger motorcyclists, as both companies announced today.
This initiative will draw attention to the importance of the helmet use, because it is ultimately the only protection element, the head injury or even death in the event of a motorcycle accident.
Michelin pointed out that this campaign is part of its commitment to the road safety, the " far more than just the design and production of products with every day safer " and reiterated that they also help with other actions educational and informative nature to this objective every day to come a step closer.
This new campaign to promote the helmet use on the motorcycle, which, under the slogan ' to be or not to be ' in a first phase posters to distribute 500 motorcycle workshops, in order to achieve the best possible spread.
Finally, Michelin stressed that the road safety " is a constant concern " of the company, and it is precisely for the reason that they are manufacturers of tyres for two - rädige vehicles ever to see that one of its main objectives of the development of safer products.
The sale of small trucks is rising again something
After nearly two years of the car market for small trucks finally some light at the end of the dark tunnel.
The 9.425 vehicles, which were approved in November in Spain, represent an increase of 12.6% in the year 2008, and, more importantly, they are the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decline, according to the manufacturers ' association Anfac and the car dealers ' association Ganvam presented figures.
These are good numbers, however, currently only with great caution, as the reference data used for comparison in November 2008, which was a particularly bad Verkausjahr with a decrease of 60% on the previous year.
However, we must remember that, apart from the increase in the last month, the overall admissions of these 11 months still 40% below the sales figures of the previous financial year.
Since January, a total of 95.853 vehicles sold in this number, but all vehicles from which the vans market is: descendants of passenger cars, pick - ups, vans, small vans and lighter vans/chassis.
Furthermore, are still the same storm clouds in the sky, most in demand, because even if some of the vehicles purchased by individuals, most of the sales to small and medium - sized enterprises, which almost 100% of all cases the purchase with a third - party financing.
So we have to these restrictions, which are the result of the tap of credit institutions, there are other factors, such as the increase in the unemployment rate or the persistence of the poor economic situation.
In this scenario, and unlike the cars, the financial support for the purchase of a vehicle of the plan 2000E little.
This plan is intended not only to individuals, the self - employed and small businesses have a right to expect that, if up to 3.5 tonnes with a CO2 emissions, not exceed 160 grams per to buy, but the low sales figures speak for themselves.
Just yesterday had Ganvam reminded that it is part of the state, including a special attention to this small and, of course, also on the industrial vehicles (trucks and buses) .
The car dealers association predicts for the 2010 a similar year just as the last, for which it with a sales (for passenger cars and SUVs) by 19%.
The support for Bremsmanövern in critical situations is now duty
As the Antiblockierbremssystem ABS and how it is happening now with the ESP stability control systems, the aid in European cars.
In fact, they are already duty on all newly registered passenger cars and light trucks, for the remaining vehicles a waiting period until the end of February 2011.
The measure adopted by the European Union aims to improve the protection of pedestrians, but these braking systems, because of their operation can also help to prevent many front - rear collisions.
The task of the Notbremsassistenten is more pressure on the brakes in the event of a critical Bremsmanövers system on the basis of the Bremsstärke carried out on the recognises.
However, this system is not that pressure until the end.
According to one of the components manufacturer for the Bosch vehicles, a third of the drivers involved in an accident before the Zusammenstoss was no longer on the Bremspedal and half of them had not slowed down with full force.
Up to 1,100 accidents
The Bremshilfe with maximum force in the braking system and the Bremszeit and therefore also the Bremsabstand, a car in the Bremsvorgang back.
According to a study by the EU could each year up to 1.100 fatal accidents involving pedestrians to damage, be prevented if all cars were equipped with this type of Notbremsassistenten.
It would be even less accidents - it is estimated that one in four accident involving personal injury could be prevented, once the so - called intelligent popularity.
Then the vehicle is equipped with a system that (on radar or a camera) obstacles and warns the driver, while at the same time, there has been a slight pressure on the brakes.
If the driver then responded, helps him the system to increase the pressure on the brake pedal, if it would be necessary.
If the driver does not react to the warning, and even if the Zusammenstoss is inevitable, the Bremsassistent the maximum pressure on the brakes, in order to keep the damage as much as possible.
