Brazil called a date to leave
The Brazilian government has set the residence of Manuel Zelaya in its embassy in Tegucigalpa a deadline.
The office of the President must leave the diplomatic representation at the latest on 27 January, when officially expires
Francisco Catunda, trade delegates of the Brazilian Embassy in the Honduran capital, confirmed the TV Globo that he knows that " Mel " before that date the message, in which he had found since 21 September asylum must have left.
" He is aware that he must go on 27 January, when his mandate expires on that day and he needs to find a new shelter. "
The station also quoted the ex - president, who confirmed his intention to leave the message before the date: " My position is to go as soon as possible, with the backing of the government of Brazil, " Zelaya said on the phone.
After the elections on 29 November (where Porfirio Lobo emerged as the victor) assured Zelaya that he will stay until January in the Brazilian Embassy.
However, he tried this week to obtain refuge in Brazil.
This, however, foundered on the refusal to recognise the status of an asylum seeker politician, the " de facto " government headed by Roberto Micheletti wanted to impose.
