Punishment over 63 million for France Télécom because of the competition.
The regulator for competition in France, France Télécom has a penalty on 63 million euros for anti - competitive behaviour in the Caribbean territories within the country.
According to the authority of the telephone providers competition in fixed and mobile phone through the signing of exclusive contracts, pricing plans and loyalty programs for the consumer on the fringes of the regulation.
Along with this sanction, the former French anti - trust and still state companies more than 560 million euros in fines since 1994 for obstructing his competitors.
The penalty was imposed even increased, as the authority, the competition watchdog, is of the opinion that France Télécom has committed in the past, and has become so again later.
Application of trade
On the other hand, the subsidiary of the French company has followed the example of other phone providers and on the Internet in order to increase the revenue ausGeschäften, not from the telephone link, a Anwendungshandelsseiteeröffnet.
In principle, this Anwndungswebseite of Orange in France and the United Kingdom.
We must wait until 2010, these Siete also in other countries, such as Spain, will be available.
